The paper discusses the implementation of synaptic memory in neuromorphic systems using Magnetic Tunnel Junctions (MTJs). This topic falls under the field of neural networks and neuromorphic computing, which is covered by the cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) sub-category. Additionally, the paper discusses the magnetization dynamics of the MTJ, which is related to the field of electromagnetics (cs.EM) and nanoelectronics (cs.NANO). The use of MTJs also falls under the category of emerging technologies (cs.ET) and magnetic materials (cs.MM).
